<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}-{2}{y}=-{22}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{2}{x}-{6}{y}=-{34}</m></p>
<p><input type="text" style="width:10.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({4},{7}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}+-{2}{y}=-{22}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}=-{22}-{\left(-{2}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{22}-{\left(-{2}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{2}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{\left(\frac{{-{22}-{\left(-{2}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{2}}}}\right)}+-{6}{y}=-{34}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{2}}{{-{{2}}}}\cdot{\left(-{22}\right)}-\frac{{2}}{{-{{2}}}}{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}+-{6}{y}=-{34}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{22}-{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}+-{6}{y}=-{34}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{y}+{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}=-{34}-{22}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{y}+{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}=-{56}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{2}+{\left(-{6}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{56}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{y}=-{56}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{56}}{{-{{8}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={7}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}+-{2}{\left({7}\right)}=-{22}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}+{\left(-{14}\right)}=-{22}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}=-{22}-{\left(-{14}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{8}}{{-{{2}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={4}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({4},{7}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
